Function: polsturm
Section: polynomials
C-Name: sturmpart
Prototype: lGDGDG
Help: polsturm(pol,{a},{b}): number of real roots of the polynomial pol in the
 interval]a,b] (which are respectively taken to be -oo or +oo when omitted)
Doc: number of real roots of the real polynomial \var{pol} in the interval
 $]a,b]$, using Sturm's algorithm. $a$ (resp.~$b$) is taken to be $-\infty$
 (resp.~$+\infty$) if omitted.
